   "source": [
    "# 3.7 扩散语言模型 (Diffusion LLM)\n",
    "\n",
    "> 🕐 预估学习时间：35分钟\n",
    "\n",
    "扩散模型在图像生成领域取得巨大成功后，2024-2025年开始被应用于语言建模，代表了一种自回归之外的全新范式。\n",
    "\n",
    "本节涵盖：\n",
    "- 扩散模型基础原理\n",
    "- 离散扩散与连续扩散\n",
    "- LLaDA / dLLM 架构\n",
    "- 自回归 vs 扩散的对比\n",
    "- 扩散 LLM 的优势与挑战"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. 为什么需要扩散语言模型？\n",
    "\n",
    "**自回归模型的局限**：\n",
    "- **串行生成**：必须从左到右逐个 token 生成，无法并行\n",
    "- **单向上下文**：只能看到左侧上下文，无法利用右侧信息\n",
    "- **错误累积**：早期错误会影响后续所有 token\n",
    "\n",
    "**扩散模型的优势**：\n",
    "- **并行生成**：可以同时生成所有 token\n",
    "- **全局上下文**：生成时考虑双向信息\n",
    "- **迭代精炼**：从噪声逐步去噪，可自我修正\n",
    "- **可控性**：可引导生成过程朝向特定属性"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. 扩散模型基础原理\n",
    "\n",
    "**核心流程**：\n",
    "1. **前向过程（加噪）**：逐步向数据添加高斯噪声，直到变为纯噪声\n",
    "   - $q(x_t | x_{t-1}) = \\mathcal{N}(x_t; \\sqrt{1-\\beta_t} x_{t-1}, \\beta_t I)$\n",
    "2. **反向过程（去噪）**：训练神经网络从噪声中恢复原始数据\n",
    "   - $p_\\theta(x_{t-1} | x_t) = \\mathcal{N}(x_{t-1}; \\mu_\\theta(x_t, t), \\Sigma_\\theta(x_t, t))$\n",
    "3. **推理生成**：从纯噪声出发，逐步去噪生成样本\n",
    "\n",
    "**在语言中的应用**：\n",
    "- **离散扩散**：对离散 token 做扩散（Mask-predict、Uniform diffusion）\n",
    "- **连续扩散**：将 token 嵌入连续空间后做扩散（LLaDA、dLLM）\n",
    "- **混合方法**：离散 token + 连续嵌入扩散"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import torch.nn.functional as F\n",
    "import math\n",
    "\n",
    "torch.manual_seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "class SimpleDiffusionLM(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, d_model=64, vocab_size=100, n_diffusion_steps=10):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "        self.d_model = d_model\n",
    "        self.vocab_size = vocab_size\n",
    "        self.n_steps = n_diffusion_steps\n",
    "\n",
    "        self.token_embed = nn.Embedding(vocab_size, d_model)\n",
    "        self.time_embed = nn.Embedding(n_diffusion_steps, d_model)\n",
    "\n",
    "        self.denoiser = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            nn.Linear(d_model * 2, 256), nn.ReLU(),\n",
    "            nn.LayerNorm(256),\n",
    "            nn.Linear(256, 128), nn.ReLU(),\n",
    "            nn.LayerNorm(128),\n",
    "            nn.Linear(128, d_model)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "        self.lm_head = nn.Linear(d_model, vocab_size)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def add_noise(self, clean_embeds, t):\n",
    "        alpha_bar = 1 - (t.float() / self.n_steps)\n",
    "        alpha_bar = alpha_bar.view(-1, 1, 1)\n",
    "        noise = torch.randn_like(clean_embeds)\n",
    "        noisy = alpha_bar.sqrt() * clean_embeds + (1 - alpha_bar).sqrt() * noise\n",
    "        return noisy, noise\n",
    "\n",
    "    def forward(self, tokens, t):\n",
    "        clean_embeds = self.token_embed(tokens)\n",
    "        noisy_embeds, noise = self.add_noise(clean_embeds, t)\n",
    "        time_embeds = self.time_embed(t).unsqueeze(1).expand(-1, tokens.shape[1], -1)\n",
    "        denoiser_input = torch.cat([noisy_embeds, time_embeds], dim=-1)\n",
    "        predicted_noise = self.denoiser(denoiser_input)\n",
    "        pred_clean = (noisy_embeds - (1 - (t.float()/self.n_steps).view(-1,1,1)).sqrt() * predicted_noise) / (1 - (t.float()/self.n_steps).view(-1,1,1)).sqrt().clamp(min=1e-4)\n",
    "        logits = self.lm_head(pred_clean)\n",
    "        return logits, noise, predicted_noise\n",
    "\n",
    "    def loss(self, tokens, t):\n",
    "        logits, noise, pred_noise = self.forward(tokens, t)\n",
    "        noise_loss = F.mse_loss(pred_noise, noise)\n",
    "        token_loss = F.cross_entropy(\n",
    "            logits.view(-1, self.vocab_size),\n",
    "            tokens.view(-1)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        return noise_loss + 0.3 * token_loss\n",
    "\n",
    "    @torch.no_grad()\n",
    "    def generate(self, seq_len, batch_size=1, n_steps=None):\n",
    "        if n_steps is None:\n",
    "            n_steps = self.n_steps\n",
    "        x = torch.randn(batch_size, seq_len, self.d_model)\n",
    "\n",
    "        for t in reversed(range(n_steps)):\n",
    "            t_tensor = torch.full((batch_size,), t, dtype=torch.long)\n",
    "            time_embeds = self.time_embed(t_tensor).unsqueeze(1).expand(-1, seq_len, -1)\n",
    "            denoiser_input = torch.cat([x, time_embeds], dim=-1)\n",
    "            pred_noise = self.denoiser(denoiser_input)\n",
    "\n",
    "            alpha_bar = 1 - (t / self.n_steps)\n",
    "            alpha_bar_prev = 1 - ((t - 1) / self.n_steps) if t > 0 else 1.0\n",
    "\n",
    "            x = (x - (1 - alpha_bar) / (1 - alpha_bar + 1e-8).sqrt() * pred_noise) / alpha_bar.sqrt()\n",
    "            if t > 0:\n",
    "                noise = torch.randn_like(x) * ((1 - alpha_bar_prev) / (1 - alpha_bar) * (1 - alpha_bar / alpha_bar_prev)).sqrt()\n",
    "                x = x + noise\n",
    "\n",
    "        logits = self.lm_head(x)\n",
    "        return logits.argmax(dim=-1)\n",
    "\n",
    "model = SimpleDiffusionLM(d_model=64, vocab_size=100, n_diffusion_steps=10)\n",
    "optimizer = torch.optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=1e-3)\n",
    "\n",
    "tokens = torch.randint(0, 100, (8, 16))\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== Diffusion Language Model Training ===')\n",
    "for epoch in range(30):\n",
    "    t = torch.randint(0, model.n_steps, (tokens.shape[0],))\n",
    "    loss = model.loss(tokens, t)\n",
    "    optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "    loss.backward()\n",
    "    torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), 1.0)\n",
    "    optimizer.step()\n",
    "    if (epoch + 1) % 10 == 0:\n",
    "        print(f'Epoch {epoch+1}: loss={loss.item():.4f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "generated = model.generate(seq_len=8, batch_size=1, n_steps=5)\n",
    "print(f'\\nGenerated tokens: {generated[0].tolist()}')\n",
    "print(f'\\nKey: Diffusion LMs generate all tokens in parallel via iterative denoising.')\n",
    "print(f'This is fundamentally different from autoregressive left-to-right generation.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. LLaDA 与 dLLM\n",
    "\n",
    "**LLaDA (Large Language Diffusion with mAsking)**：\n",
    "- 8B 参数的扩散语言模型\n",
    "- 使用 mask-predict 范式：随机 mask token，训练模型恢复\n",
    "- 在多个 benchmark 上达到与 LLaMA-8B 相当的性能\n",
    "- 生成速度可随扩散步数灵活调节\n",
    "\n",
    "**dLLM（扩散大语言模型）**：\n",
    "- 连续空间扩散 + 嵌入空间建模\n",
    "- 支持文本引导生成、插值等图像扩散模型的能力\n",
    "\n",
    "**关键发现**：\n",
    "- 扩散模型在 scaled-up 后能接近自回归性能\n",
    "- 推理时步数可灵活调节（步数少=速度快，步数多=质量高）\n",
    "- 天然支持 infilling（文本补全）和双向生成"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def compare_ar_vs_diffusion():\n",
    "    seq_len = 128\n",
    "    n_diffusion_steps = 32\n",
    "    ar_flops_per_token = 1e9\n",
    "    diff_flops_per_step = 1e9\n",
    "\n",
    "    ar_total_flops = seq_len * ar_flops_per_token\n",
    "    diff_total_flops = n_diffusion_steps * diff_flops_per_step\n",
    "\n",
    "    print('=== Autoregressive vs Diffusion LM ===')\n",
    "    print(f'Sequence length: {seq_len}')\n",
    "    print(f'\\nAutoregressive:')\n",
    "    print(f'  Generation: {seq_len} serial steps')\n",
    "    print(f'  Total FLOPS: {ar_total_flops/1e9:.1f}G')\n",
    "    print(f'  Context: Unidirectional (left only)')\n",
    "    print(f'  Generation speed: Fixed')\n",
    "    print(f'\\nDiffusion ({n_diffusion_steps} steps):')\n",
    "    print(f'  Generation: {n_diffusion_steps} parallel steps')\n",
    "    print(f'  Total FLOPS: {diff_total_flops/1e9:.1f}G')\n",
    "    print(f'  Context: Bidirectional')\n",
    "    print(f'  Generation speed: Adjustable (trade steps for quality)')\n",
    "    print(f'\\nFLOPS ratio: {diff_total_flops/ar_total_flops:.2f}x')\n",
    "\n",
    "    if diff_total_flops < ar_total_flops:\n",
    "        print(f'Diffusion is MORE efficient for long sequences.')\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(f'Diffusion has higher total FLOPS but is fully parallelizable.')\n",
    "        print(f'On GPUs, parallelism can hide this overhead.')\n",
    "\n",
    "compare_ar_vs_diffusion()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'\\nKey: Diffusion trades more FLOPS for parallelism and bidirectionality.')\n",
    "print(f'For short sequences, AR wins; for long sequences, diffusion may win.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. 扩散 LLM 的挑战与前景\n",
    "\n",
    "**当前挑战**：\n",
    "- **性能差距**：在大部分 benchmark 上仍落后于同规模自回归模型\n",
    "- **训练效率**：需要多步扩散训练，收敛较慢\n",
    "- **生态不成熟**：推理框架、量化工具等不如自回归丰富\n",
    "\n",
    "**前景展望**：\n",
    "- **混合架构**：自回归生成主干 + 扩散解码细粒度 token\n",
    "- **推理加速**：蒸馏 + 少步采样（如 4 步生成媲美 256 步）\n",
    "- **特殊场景**：infilling、可控生成、文本编辑等双向任务\n",
    "\n",
    "**代表工作**：LLaDA、dLLM、MDLM、DiffuSeq、Diffusion-LM、D3PM"
   ]
  },
